      "id": "PopularPost331142",
      "post_content": "While entering play tapped is a major drawback, having to return a land to your hand doesn't matter. You can tap it first to put mana into your pool, so the only loss you get is the Boilerworks entering tapped. While this does mean that you won't have that mana open for counters on their next turn, if you are playing Boilerworks you probably aren't having a very central \"draw go\" strategy anyway. The point is, this is a very good land that can give you card advantage and get your ahead on mana.  \n  \n4/5",
